pe":"text","value":".","position":{"start":{"line":73,"column":1},"end":{"line":73,"column":1}},"key":"es3J0fy9zo"}],"key":"ctvLoHkiAc"},{"type":"container","kind":"figure","children":[{"type":"image","url":"/build/spyder_run_configura-dbd6f7aea6160803d0cd534be485b5db.png","alt":"Spyder run configuration showing execution in an external system terminal as well as allowing interaction with the Python console after execution.","align":"center","data":{"altTextIsAutoGenerated":true},"key":"mtVFHkjpAO","urlSource":"figures/spyder_run_configuration.png"},{"type":"caption","children":[{"type":"paragraph","position":{"start":{"line":79,"column":1},"end":{"line":79,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"captionNumber","kind":"figure","label":"fig:spyder_configuration","identifier":"fig:spyder_configuration","html_id":"fig-spyder-configuration","enumerator":"2.1","children":[{"type":"text","value":"Figure ","key":"ATfsaNPorn"},{"type":"text","value":"2.1","key":"bOJ37pORxE"},{"type":"text","value":":","key":"nKminEFvJm"}],"template":"Figure %s:","key":"jTS8rez1Yv"},{"type":"text","value":"Spyder run configuration showing execution in an external system terminal as well as allowing interaction with the Python console after execution.","position":{"start":{"line":79,"column":1},"end":{"line":79,"column":1}},"key":"zUI2ZVajSk"}],"key":"Yv67SUiKy9"}],"key":"CasPZrwFqJ"}],"label":"fig:spyder_configuration","identifier":"fig:spyder_configuration","enumerator":"2.1","html_id":"fig-spyder-configuration","key":"GkzasCbEgK"},{"type":"heading","depth":3,"position":{"start":{"line":82,"column":1},"end":{"line":82,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Computational Requirements","position":{"start":{"line":82,"column":1},"end":{"line":82,"column":1}},"key":"rGnDgipgka"}],"identifier":"computational-requirements","label":"Computational Requirements","html_id":"computational-requirements","implicit":true,"enumerator":"2.3","key":"hjC4awG11u"},{"type":"paragraph","position":{"start":{"line":84,"column":1},"end":{"line":84,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Rattlesnake is a process-heavy software; it spawns processes for each environment, as well as for various portions of the controller that should operate in parallel.  In general, the core controller utilizes 2-3 full processes.  Various environments will also utilize multiple processes; for example, the ","key":"T83OFDStPM"},{"type":"abbreviation","title":"Multiple Input, Multiple Output","children":[{"type":"text","value":"MIMO","key":"g8ReLdcaRZ"}],"key":"FgX1aVfQRV"},{"type":"text","value":" Random Vibration uses 3 main processes to compute spectral quantities (","key":"ZY8d9w7sjS"},{"type":"abbreviation","title":"Frequency Response Function","children":[{"type":"text","value":"FRF","key":"e2e7nijct3"}],"key":"DREqlJPlB0"},{"type":"text","value":"s, ","key":"CzhfFA9axr"},{"type":"abbreviation","title":"Cross-Power Spectral Density","children":[{"type":"text","value":"CPSD","key":"UJbalf9LDS"}],"key":"JzcKIW9J8i"},{"type":"text","value":"s, etc.), perform control calculations, and generate time histories simultaneously.  If running virtual control, keep in mind that acquisition processes will be more fully subscribed due to the need to integrate the equations of motion rather than just read data off the data acquisition hardware.","key":"CA4sx1nOT1"}],"key":"k61SLAtj1e"},{"type":"paragraph","position":{"start":{"line":86,"column":1},"end":{"line":86,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"While the exact computational requirements will depend on the channel count of the test and size of the control computations, the authors have had success using a 6-core processor with 32 GB RAM for multi-environment control approximately 20 control channels and 4 outputs.  For a 200 acquisition channel test with 50 control channels and 8 outputs, the authors needed to upgrade to a 16 core, 32 GB RAM computer.","position":{"start":{"line":86,"column":1},"end":{"line":86,"column":1}},"key":"KhSeqX9gqI"}],"key":"iw1eFz3jye"},{"type":"heading","depth":3,"position":{"start":{"line":89,"column":1},"end":{"line":89,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Obtaining Support","position":{"start":{"line":89,"column":1},"end":{"line":89,"column":1}},"key":"ZwIV9pmCLE"}],"label":"sec:obtaining_support","identifier":"sec:obtaining_support","html_id":"sec-obtaining-support","enumerator":"2.4","key":"GUqmcbdhVC"},{"type":"paragraph","position":{"start":{"line":91,"column":1},"end":{"line":91,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Rattlesnake was developed by a small team as a research tool, and as such will not be as polished as commercial vibration software.  Therefore, it should be expected that bugs and errors will occur from time to time.  If a bug occurs, please report it by creating a new issue in the ","position":{"start":{"line":91,"column":1},"end":{"line":91,"column":1}},"key":"znzgZkMVs1"},{"type":"link","url":"https://github.com/sandialabs/rattlesnake-vibration-controller/issues","position":{"start":{"line":91,"column":1},"end":{"line":91,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"GitHub issues board","position":{"start":{"line":91,"column":1},"end":{"line":91,"column":1}},"key":"nHv0ZUKHfZ"}],"urlSource":"https://github.com/sandialabs/rattlesnake-vibration-controller/issues","error":true,"key":"wfahBLKwYd"},{"type":"text","value":".  This will notify the development team of the issue and they can work to solve it.  If users have a feature request, these can also be submitted to the ","position":{"start":{"line":91,"column":1},"end":{"line":91,"column":1}},"key":"pIyc2wjow9"},{"type":"link","url":"https://github.com/sandialabs/rattlesnake-vibration-controller/issues","position":{"start":{"line":91,"column":1},"end":{"line":91,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"GitHub issues board","position":{"start":{"line":91,"column":1},"end":{"line":91,"column":1}},"key":"m9ores27eU"}],"urlSource":"https://github.com/sandialabs/rattlesnake-vibration-controller/issues","error":true,"key":"cKV8zYmG5M"},{"type":"text","value":".","position":{"start":{"line":91,"column":1},"end":{"line":91,"column":1}},"key":"gakEZHJCxa"}],"key":"piFrduyc3f"},{"type":"paragraph","position":{"start":{"line":93,"column":1},"end":{"line":93,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"The issue tracker provides templates for Bugs, Feature Requests, and Questions.  The more thoroughly that these can be filled out, the greater the chance that the development team can solve the issue.  For bug reports, files can also be attached to the issue, so the users can include the ","position":{"start":{"line":93,"column":1},"end":{"line":93,"column":1}},"key":"xOQ3SZWqd8"},{"type":"inlineCode","value":"Rattlesnake.log","position":{"start":{"line":93,"column":1},"end":{"line":93,"column":1}},"key":"pEvfeT3stP"},{"type":"text","value":" file that is generated for each run of the Rattlesnake, as well as any screenshot of error messages that get shown in dialog boxes or the command window.  The question template can be used for basic support questions, which will be answered by the developers as their time permits.  Users should certainly consult this User’s Manual and the Rattlesnake Source Code first to ensure their question is not covered by it.","position":{"start":{"line":93,"column":1},"end":{"line":93,"column":1}},"key":"CUw5sfOeDB"}],"key":"EZKp2vMs6E"}],"key":"Gairk3qC5r"}],"key":"lLVWWrHYxt"},"references":{"cite":{"order":[],"data":{}}},"footer":{"navigation":{"prev":{"title":"Part 1: Rattlesnake Overview","url":"/part-1","group":"Rattlesnake Vibration Controller"},"next":{"title":"Using Rattlesnake","url":"/chapter-03","group":"Rattlesnake Vibration Controller"}}},"domain":"http://localhost:3000"}